From 0bfcd8df57f619d20be6e3f5668c66bf58af221f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium Build <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 16:11:48 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 03/14] chronium: seeded canvas pixel noise in toDataURL and
 toBlob
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds the first real anti-detect surface patch: HTMLCanvasElement
readback now produces per-profile-deterministic but cross-profile-
divergent pixel data, defeating canvas fingerprinting that hashes
toDataURL/toBlob output.

New: blink::FingerprintState (third_party/blink/renderer/platform/
fingerprint/) — a renderer-process-wide holder for the seed received
from the browser via Mojo (patch 0002). First setter wins, all-zero
seeds are rejected. Exposes HashAt(channel, x, y) — a deterministic
32-bit hash mixing the seed with a per-surface channel name plus
coordinates. Same (profile, channel, x, y) -> same hash forever.

Hook: chrome/renderer/chrome_render_frame_observer.cc's Mojo
GetConfig callback now calls FingerprintState::Set instead of just
logging.

Patch: HTMLCanvasElement::ToDataURLInternal and toBlob now run the
Snapshot through ApplyCanvasFingerprintNoise (file-local helper).
For each pixel, HashAt('canvas', x, y) selects ~1 in 256 pixels and
flips the LSB of one of R/G/B (alpha untouched). Visually
imperceptible, cryptographically detectable: tested with two
fingerprint profiles, toDataURL hash differs and PNG length differs.

Known limitation: race between DidCreateNewDocument firing the
GetConfig Mojo call and the document's inline scripts. A canvas
fingerprint read SYNCHRONOUSLY from a top-level <script> on first
load may run before the Mojo response arrives, in which case
IsActive() is false and ApplyCanvasFingerprintNoise returns the
input unchanged. The next read (after any await/setTimeout) sees
the seed and is noised. To fix in a follow-up patch by passing the
seed to renderer processes via a command-line switch instead of
async Mojo.

Files touched:
- third_party/blink/renderer/platform/fingerprint/
    fingerprint_state.{h,cc}                  (new)
- third_party/blink/renderer/platform/BUILD.gn  (register sources)
- chrome/renderer/chrome_render_frame_observer.cc
                                                (push seed to blink)
- third_party/blink/renderer/core/html/canvas/html_canvas_element.cc
                                                (apply noise pre-encode)

Verified: profile A hash -718601788 (len 1562), profile B hash
1834648629 (len 1838). Same profile across 3 reads -> same hash.
